                            <comment id="13581615" author="kristwaa" created="Tue, 19 Feb 2013 20:52:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch 1a shows how the functionality can be implemented.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I tested it by specifying an invalid value for derbyTesting.oldReleasePath and running the upgrade tests with junit-single:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$ ant -DderbyTesting.oldReleasePath=/asdasd7asdasd -Dderby.junit.testclass=org.apache.derbyTesting.functionTests.tests.upgradeTests._Suite junit-single&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
junit-single:&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;junit&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ALARM: Non-existing location for jar files: &apos;/asdasd7asdasd\10.0.2.1&apos;. Upgrade tests can NOT be run!&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13582276" author="knutanders" created="Wed, 20 Feb 2013 16:11:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like a useful improvement. +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13582445" author="kristwaa" created="Wed, 20 Feb 2013 19:24:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed patch 1a to trunk with revision 1448359.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13668181" author="knutanders" created="Tue, 28 May 2013 09:34:37 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I merged the fix to 10.9 and committed revision 1486816.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I plan to use it to pass the derby.tests.basePort property to the Jenkins build jobs to prevent port conflicts, as discussed in this thread: &lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/db-derby-dev/201305.mbox/%3C51A4333E.7040801%40oracle.com%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/db-derby-dev/201305.mbox/%3C51A4333E.7040801%40oracle.com%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
